  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is the most common disorder among childhood sexual abuse
      survivors and is associated with substantial psychosocial and medical problems, but
      evidence-based treatment for PTSD in adolescents is lacking. This study aims to examine the
      efficacy and effectiveness of prolonged exposure therapy for adolescents with client-centered
      therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
